thread.title: Maureen O’Hara, star from Hollywood’s Golden Age, dies

author: Associated Press
title: Maureen O’Hara, star from Hollywood’s Golden Age, dies
text:
Photo: Nbc, NBCU Photo Bank Via Getty Images MAUREEN O'HARA -- Pictured: Actress Maureen O'Hara in 1943 -- (Photo by: NBC/NBCU Photo Bank via Getty Images) MAUREEN O'HARA -- Pictured: Actress Maureen O'Hara in 1943 --...
LOS ANGELES — Fiery-haired and feisty, Maureen O’Hara could handle anything the world and Hollywood threw at her. Director John Ford punched her in the jaw at a party and John Wayne dragged her through sheep dung — real sheep dung — in “The Quiet Man.” In “Miracle on 34th Street” she learned to believe in Santa Claus.
